<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="1" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72110/8937: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-06T20:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                        1920—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:47
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>205. Should I attend prospective meeting of Premiers in London if invited
                            and, if so, under what instructions?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>